2019ud reported: I prayed with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, while Abu Bakr and Umar were with him. When I sat down, I began by praising Allah, then sending blessings upon the Prophet, then supplicating for myself. The Prophet said, \u201cAsk and you will be\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11580,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/22\/dua-salat-ala-al-nabi-most\/","url_meta":{"origin":15329,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Salawat: Nearest to Prophet blessed him most","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 22, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Mas\u2019ud reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe closest of people to me on the Day of Resurrection are those who sent the most blessings upon me.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 484 Grade: Hasan (fair) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0633\u0652\u0639\u064f\u0648\u062f\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33174,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/11\/prophet-sacrifices-eid-al-adha\/","url_meta":{"origin":15329,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Adha: The Prophet sacrifices an animal on Eid al-Adha","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 11, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Jabir ibn Abdullah reported: I was present with the Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, on Eid al-Adha at the place of prayer. When the Prophet finished his sermon, he came down from his pulpit and a ram was brought to him. The Prophet slaughtered it with his own\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":37235,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2021\/10\/27\/umar-dua-salat-ala-nabi\/","url_meta":{"origin":15329,"position":4},"title":"Umar on Dua: Supplication held back until the Prophet is blessed","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 27, 2021","format":false,"excerpt":"Sa\u2019id ibn al-Musayyib reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cVerily, the supplication is suspended between the heavens and the earth. Nothing ascends from it until you send blessings upon your Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 486 Grade: Sahih li ghayrihi\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":11578,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/01\/22\/bakhil-refuse-bless-prophet\/","url_meta":{"origin":15329,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Salawat: Misers refuse to bless the Prophet","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 22, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Ali ibn Abi Talib reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cThe miser is one in whose presence I am mentioned, but he does not send blessings upon me.\" Source: Sunan al-Tirmidhi\u0304 3546 Grade:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Tirmidhi \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0644\u0650\u064a\u0650\u0651 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0623\u064e\u0628\u0650\u064a \u0637\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0628\u064d \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0651 \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0647\u064f \u0639\u064e\u0644\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0647\u0650\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15329","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=15329"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/15329\/revisions"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=15329"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=15329"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=15329"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\